            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Gulai Ikan Patin is a traditional Indonesian dish featuring catfish cooked in a rich and aromatic curry sauce.
                    The catfish is typically simmered in a blend of spices such as turmeric, ginger, galangal, and 
                    lemongrass, along with coconut milk for creaminess. The dish often includes ingredients like shallots, 
                    garlic, kaffir lime leaves, and red chilies, imparting depth of flavor and a hint of heat. Gulai Ikan Patin 
                    is known for its comforting and hearty nature, making it a favorite dish in Indonesian cuisine, especially 
                    enjoyed with steamed rice.
                </p>
