            <div class="Instructions">
                <h3>Instructions</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Cut the catfish according to preference and set aside.</li>
                    <li>Grind shallots, garlic, red chilies, ginger, and turmeric into a smooth paste. Crush the galangal and lemongrass.</li>
                    <li>Heat oil in a pot and sautÃ© the spice paste until fragrant. Add kaffir lime leaves, turmeric leaves, crushed lemongrass, galangal, and sliced wild starfruits. Stir-fry until the spices are well blended and fragrant.</li>
                    <li>Add the catfish pieces and stir until coated with the spices.</li>
                    <li>Pour in the thin coconut milk and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring to prevent the coconut milk from curdling.</li>
                    <li>Season with salt and seasoning according to taste. Gradually pour in the thick coconut milk while stirring continuously. Simmer until boiling and the catfish is fully cooked.</li>
                    <li>Adjust the seasoning if needed. Serve hot with steamed rice.</li>
